
LINUX COMMAND -LS


1. ls -l :-FOR  LONG LISTENING 
2. ls -lt  :-shows the newest file come at the top.
3. ls -ltr :-shows the newest file at the bottom.
4. ls -l :- give the ascending  order based on dictionary.
5. ls -lr :- give descending order based on dictonary.
6. ls -LR :- recursively print all the directoires also
7. cal gives you the date of the calender
8. ls -a shows all the hidden files.
9.-LatR  : L is giving you the long listing
           a is giving you the hidden files 
           t is give you the newest file at the top
           R recursively print all the files
